column1:
Quantity slaughtered:
The quantity slaughtered in commercial slaughtering of
animals of domestic origin includes the quantity slaughtered
regarding animals of foreign origin.

From 2009:
Due to a new EU regulation concerning livestock and meat
statistics that took effect in 2009, the definitions of some
variables have changed; consequently, comparisons with
previous years can be made only in part.
This refers to:
Calves = up to 8 months (in the past, calves were defined as
         cattle with a live weight of up to 300 kg which did
         not have their second teeth yet).
Young cattle = more than 8, but not more than 12 months (in
               the past, this category was covered under
               bulls or female cattle).
Cattle: Not shown any longer.
